result.execSummary:
Clinton C. Rude was extradited to another county, state or jurisdiction. Extradition means Clinton C. Rude was accused or convicted of an offense in another county, state or jurisdiction and was taken there to face their charge(s) or conviction.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Letter to Governor with Copy of Extradition Order, Consent, Complaint and Fugitive Warrant.

02:04 PM Defendant Clinton C. Rude appeared by zoom technology by video means from the Pepin County Jail. Prosecuting Atty Jon D. Seifert appeared for State of Wisconsin appears by phone means.  A warrant was issued from the State of Minnesota from Wilkin County alleging 3 matters that you failed to appear.  Mr. Rude agrees he is the subject of those warrants.  Advised of right to an attorney.  Have a choice to test the warrant by 1)Habias Corpus process.  2)Refuse to be extradited and the State of WI would ask State of MN for Governor's warrant; or 3) Go back to Wilkin County and waive extradition.  Defendant requests option 3.  Court asks the jail officer have Mr. Rude sign the waiver.  By you signing that document I will find you KVI waived right to an attorney and extradition.  Jailer verifies Mr. Rudge signed the waiver of extradition.  Court will sign the Order waiving extradition.
Attached to complaint - Warrant from Wilkin County, MN
